modules.description: This module defines functions for running asynchronous test suites and constructing test cases that accept configuration arguments or run synchronously. It works with Lwt promises, Cmdliner terms, and MirageOS-compatible test structures. Use it to execute MirageOS-compatible test suites with CLI configuration or resource management via Lwt_switch.

Alcotest_mirage supports testing asynchronous functions that return Lwt promises, integrating with MirageOS and Cmdliner for CLI-driven test execution. It provides combinators to define and run test cases that may depend on configuration or resources, handling both synchronous and asynchronous behaviors. Key operations include constructing test suites with `Alcotest_mirage.test_case` and running them via `Make.run`, which schedules execution and captures exceptions. Example usage includes writing MirageOS-compatible test binaries that execute assertions and print results to the console.
